external_knowledge:
- Points per game is a measure of a player's scoring average, calculated by dividing the total points scored by the number of games played; 
- Injury level may imply the severity or the number of injuries a player has had, affecting their performance; 
- Training regimen (strength training and cardio) is crucial for player recovery and performance enhancement; 
- Team statistics are important for understanding how individual performance contributes to team success.
